  <original-body>A great feature was added in Rails 3, the hability to easily personalize the output of the generators for each application, this can improve the productivity in many cases.
I missed this functionality for a long time, since I worked with Grails for some time, and now I think only a small piece of the grails functionality is still missing.
in Grails there is a task called &quot;install-templates&quot; that copies the default templates to the personalization folder.
I created a rake task and published it in gist to do this http://gist.github.com/396453
I`m attaching a patch with this template too.
The rake task name I created is templates:copy</original-body>
